                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d01">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#17v #88r #88v #105r #145r #163v #164r"/> (multiple full stops)</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a01">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#iv(erso)"/> Compilation composed of the beginnings of various prayers. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>  ዘለአለም፡ ሥላሴ፡ ስቡህ፡ ወውዱስ፡ ዘሳረረ፡ ኩሉ፡ ዓለመ፡ በአሐቲ ቃል፡ ቅ፡ ቅ፡ ቅ እግዚአብሔር፡ አማልከ፡ አማልክት፡ ዘሐሎ፡ ወይሄሉ፡ ወትረ፡ በሰማይ፡ ወበምድር፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> 
                              </foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a02">
                           <desc type="Asmat">
                              <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/>Asmat prayer of Jeremiah the prophet against eye disease, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ዓይን፡</foreign> Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>  ጸሎት፡ ዘጸለየ፡ ኤርምያስ፡ ነቢይ፡ ኀበ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወይቤሎ፡ ኃበኒ፡ ፈውስ፡ ቤጣ፡ የውጣ፡ ጸጽና፡ ፡ ጥ፡ በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ አድህኖ፡ ወፈውሶ፡ ህማመ፡ ዓይን፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> 
                              </foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a03">
                           <desc type="Asmat">
                              <locus target="#iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto)"/> Asmat prayer told to Saint Andrew by our Lord when he sent him to a cannibalistic people to deliver Matthias.Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>  አስማት፡ ዘነገሮ፡ እግዚአነ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ረድ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ወሰማዕት፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>  ወይቤሎ፡ ሁር፡ ሀገረ፡ በላእተ፡ ሰብእ፡ ኀበ፡ ሐሎ፡ እሁከ፡ ማትያስ፡ ከመ፡ ታውጽኦ፡ እምቤተ፤ ሞቅህ፡...</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a04">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="#145r"/>, Excerpt from Image of Saint George, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መልክአ፡ ጊዮርጊስ።</foreign> Text <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለጣዕመ፡ ስምከ፡ ዘያሜንን፡ ወይነ። ወዘያረስዕ፡ ሐዘነ።ቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘተሰመይከ፡ መድህነ። በባህር፡ ወበየብስ፡ ተራድአኒ፡ ፍጡነ። እስመ፡ ኪያከ፡ ተወከልኩ፡ አነ።</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a05">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="# 164rv"/> 
                              <title type="complete" ref="LIT3089RepCh369"/>, written in a later hand, in blue ink. Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኦ፡ ሰማዕተ፡ አልፋ። ስዕለትየ፡ ወኢትግድፋ።</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a06">
                           <desc type="GuestText">
                              <locus target="# 164v–164r"/> 
                              <title type="complete" ref="LIT3100RepCh380"/> “O who is quick for help,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኦ፡ ፍጡነ፡ ረድኤት።</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a07">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/> “It is written 1929, Ḫədar 9”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e01">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ivv(erso)"/> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a08">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#105r"/> and passim mentions the scribe’s name, Gäbrä Ṣadǝq</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a09">
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                              <locus target="#166r"/> Secondary owner, Gäbrä Ḥǝywät</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#166v"/> List of the Psalms used to introduce the sections of Wisest of the Wise, in a later hand, in blue ink</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e02">
                           <desc>Identified in the insurance hand list as Religio-Magical 11.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e03">
                           <desc>Numbered quires: quires 2–17</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e04">
                           <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#18r #21r #32r #55r #60v"/>, etc.);
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#108v"/>, line 4; <locus target="#138r"/>, line 4);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#14v #40r #123r #158r"/>)</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
